REST over HTTP

The Most Common use of Rest is over HTTP.
We can Leverage HTTP methods for Crud Operations

    POST    : Whenever you send a POST request, this will Translate to CRUD operation to create and Entity.
    GET     : When you send a GET Request, this will translate the CRUD operation to read the Entity.
    PUT     : When you send a PUT Request, this will translate the CRUD operation to Update the Existing Entity.
    DELETE  : When you send a DELETE Request, this will translate the CRUD operation to Delete the Existing Entity.


HTTP Message:
                     
                        HTTP Request Message
                -----------------------------------------> 
    CRM App                                                  CRM Rest Service 
                <-----------------------------------------
                        HTTP Response Message


HTTP Request Message:

    HTTP request Message Contains:
        1. Request Line         --> has actual HTTP command(GET/POST/PUT/DELETE)
        2. Header Variables     --> Metadata
        3. Message Body         --> Content of the Message as JSON


    HTTP Response Message Contains:
        1. Response Line            --> Contains Server Protocol and Status Code
        2. Header Variable          --> Response metadata
        3. Message Body             --> contents of message


    Status Code:

        100 -199 : informational
        200 -299 : Success
        300 -399 : redirection
        400 -499 : Client Side Error
        500 -599 : Server Side Error


    MIME Content Type:

            It is the message format for actual Payload
            MIME: Multipurpose Internet Mail-Extension

            basic Syntax: type/subtype
            Example: text/html, text/plain


Here we use a Tool Called POSTMAN which will help us to send HTTP request to the Rest WebService.

POSTMAN: Rest Client.


